Czech Stocks: Erste, New World Resources Move in Prague Trading

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-12-05T16:40:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-05/czech-stocks-erste-new-world-resources-move-in-prague-trading.html
The  Czech Republic ’s  PX (PX)  equity index
increased 1.5 percent to 901.1 by the close of trading in
 Prague , adding to a 5.4 percent advance last week.  The following were among the most active stocks on the
Prague Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Erste Group Bank AG (RBAG)   of Austria gained 4.7 percent
to 348.7 koruna, after a 16 percent advance last week. Lenders
led a rally in European stocks as Italian Prime Minister Mario
Monti’s proposal to cut his nation’s debt boosted demand for
riskier assets worldwide.  New World Resources Plc (NWR)  , the biggest coking-coal
producer in the Czech Republic, rose a second day, increasing
2.2 percent to 134.85 koruna.  Europe ’s benchmark coal
 derivatives  increased 0.7 percent to $116 a metric ton, a two-
week high, in the Netherlands.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
